p: Pure biodiesel (B100) had 36 MJ/kg before the AOM assay; after it, the HHV of the samples was measured in the presence and absence of the extract. The oxidized biodiesel (B100 ox) showed an HHV decrease of 14% compared to the original value of HHV of biodiesel (B100). The samples with antioxidant added did not show any significant changes. The results are listed in Table 4. On the other hand, the pure extract had an HHV of 23.6 MJ/kg. There is a small quantity of extract in biodiesel (1 g/L at the most); consequently, the possibility of reducing biodiesel HHV through the addition of extract is dismissed.
